ooks?id=7dwMAQAAMAAJ&dq=Baybars+II+mamluk+of+Qalawun&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22all+Mamluks+of+Qalawun%22}}</ref> Relative to  Husam ad-Din Lajin{{sfn|Yosef|2012b|p=396}}\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#b2dfdf\"\n|14th\n|Al-Malik an-Nasir\n|Nasir ad-Din Muhammad\n|5 March 1310<ref name=\"Stewart86\"/>\n|6 June 1341<ref name=\"Stewart86\"/>\n|Kipchak Turk\n|Third reign.\n|[[File:Gold dinar of an-Nasir Muhammad.jpg|100x100px]]\n|- bgcolor=\"#b2dfdf\"\n|15th\n|Al-Malik al-Mansur\n|[[Saif ad-Din Abu-Bakr|Sayf ad-Din Abu Bakr]]\n|8 June 1341<ref name=\"Stewart86\"/>\n|August 1341<ref name=\"Drory20\">Drory 2006, p. 20.</ref>\n|Kipchak Turk\n|Son of an-Nasir Muhammad and his concubine Narjis.<ref name=\"Bauden63\">Bauden 2009, p. 63.</ref> Real power in Abu Bakr's sultanate was held by Qawsun, a ''mamluk'' and senior [[emir]] of an-Nasir Muhammad.<ref name=\"Drory20\"/>\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#b2dfdf\"\n|16th\n|Al-Malik al-Ashraf\n|[[Kujuk|Ala'a ad-Din Kujuk]]\n|August 1341<ref>Levanoni 1995, p. 102.</ref>\n|21 January 1342<ref name=\"Drory24\">Drory 2006, p. 24.</ref>\n|Kipchak Turk and [[Tatars|Tatar]]\n|Son of an-Nasir Muhammad and his Tatar concubine Ardu.<ref name=\"Bauden63\"/> An infant when he was made sultan by strongman Qawsun.<ref name=\"Drory20\"/>\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#b2dfdf\"\n|17th\n|Al-Malik an-Nasir\n|[[An-Nasir Ahmad, Sultan of Egypt|Shihab ad-Din Ahmad]]\n|21 January 1342<ref name=\"Drory24\"/>\n|27 June 1342<ref name=\"Drory28\">Drory 2006, p. 28.</ref>\n|Kipchak Turk\n|Son of an-Nasir Muhammad and his concubine Bayad, a freed slave girl.<ref name=\"Bauden63\"/>\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#b2dfdf\"\n|18th\n|Al-Malik as-Salih\n|[[As-Salih Ismail, Sultan of Egypt|Imad ad-Din Abu'l Fida Isma'il]]\n|27 June 1342<ref name=\"Drory24\"/>\n|3 August 1345<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\">{{cite book|editor1-last=Chisholm|editor1-first=Hugh|title=The Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica: A Dictionary of Arts, Sciences, Literature and General Information, Volume IX|date=1910|publisher=The Encyclop\u00e