rcassian\n|Son of Barquq.<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|33rd\n|Al-Malik an-Nasir\n|[[An-Nasir Faraj|Nasir ad-Din Faraj]]\n|November 1405<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|23 May 1412<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|Second reign.\n|[[File:Gold dinar of an-Nasir Faraj.jpg|100x100px]]\n|- bgcolor=\"#ffffff\"\n|34th\n|Al-Malik al-Adil\n|[[Al-Musta'in (Cairo)|Al-Musta'in Billah]]\n|23 May 1412<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|6 November 1412<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|[[Arab]]\n|The ''Caliph of Cairo'' was appointed by the Burji emir Shaykh Mahmudi as a figurehead, but then compelled him to abdicate.<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|35th\n|Al-Malik al-Mu'ayyad\n|[[Shaykh al-Mahmudi]]\n|6 November 1412<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|13 January 1421<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|A ''mamluk'' of Barquq.\n|[[File:Gold dinar of Shaykh al-Mahmudi.jpg|100x100px]]\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|36th\n|Al-Malik al-Muzaffar\n|[[Al-Muzaffar Ahmad|Ahmad]]\n|13 January 1421<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|29 August 1421<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|Son of Shaykh. Was an infant during accession.\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|37th\n|Al-Malik az-Zahir\n|[[Sayf ad-Din Tatar]]\n|29 August 1421<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|30 November 1421<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|A ''mamluk'' of Barquq<ref name=\"Garcin293\">Garcin, ed. Petry 1998, p. 293.</ref>\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|38th\n|Al-Malik as-Salih\n|[[An-Nasir ad-Din Muhammad]]\n|30 November 1421<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|1 April 1422<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|Son of Tatar. Was an infant during accession.<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|39th\n|Al-Malik al-Ashraf\n|[[Barsbay|Sayf ad-Din Barsbay]]\n|1 April 1422<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|7 June 1438<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|A ''mamluk'' of Barquq.<ref name=\"Garcin293\"/> He was a tutor of Muhammad before he toppled him.<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|[[File:Barsbay gold ashrafi 1422 1438.jpg|100x100px]]\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|40th\n|Al-Malik al-Aziz\n|[[Al-Aziz Jamal ad-Din Yusuf|Jamal ad-Din Abu al-Mahasin Yusuf]]\n|7 June 1438<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|9 September 1438<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|Son of Barsbay. Was a child during accession.\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|41st\n|Al-Malik az-Zahir\n|[[Sayf ad-Din Jaqmaq]]\n|9 September 1438<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|1 February 1453<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|A ''mamluk'' of Barquq.<ref name=\"Garcin293\"/>\n|[[File:Gold dinar of Jaqmaq.jpg|100x100px]]\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|42nd\n|Al-Malik al-Mansur\n|[[Al-Mansur Fakhr-ad-Din Uthman|Fakhr ad-Din Uthman]]\n|1 February 1453<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|15 March 1453<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|Son of Jaqmaq.<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|43rd\n|Al-Malik al-Ashraf\n|[[Sayf ad-Din Inal]]\n|15 March 1453<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|26 February 1461<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|A ''mamluk'' of Barquq.<ref name=\"Garcin293\"/>\n|[[File:Silver dirham of Sayf ad-Din Inal.jpg|100x100px]]\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|44th\n|Al-Malik al-Mu'ayyad\n|[[Al-Mu'ayyad Shihab al-Din Ahmad|Shihab ad-Din Ahmad]]\n|26 February 1461<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|28 June 1461<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Circassian\n|Son of Inal.<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|45th\n|Al-Malik az-Zahir\n|[[Sayf ad-Din Khushqadam]]\n|28 June 1461<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|9 October 1467<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|Greek<ref name=\"Britannica101-103\"/>\n|A ''mamluk'' of Shaykh.<ref name=\"Garcin293\"/>\n|[[File:Gold dinar of Khushqadam.jpg|100x100px]]\n|- bgcolor=\"#fffab4\"\n|45th\n|Al-Malik az-Zahir\n|[[Sayf ad-Din Bilbay]]\n|9 October 1467<ref