ge)|Forth]]-like programming language used in the 1980s by a high school in the city of [[Oulu]].\n|\n|-\n|Tampio\n|Made to look like a natural language. Object oriented.\n|[https://github.com/fergusq/tampio]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |French\n|GOTO++\n|An esoteric programming language loosely based on French and English.\n|[http://www.gotopp.org/index.html.en]\n|-\n|[[Linotte]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[LSE (programming language)|LSE]] (Language Symbolique d'Enseignement)\n|A pedagogical programming language designed in the 1970s at the \u00c9cole Sup\u00e9rieure d'\u00c9lectricit\u00e9. A kind of BASIC, but with procedures, functions, and local variables, like in Pascal.\n|\n|-\n|BASICOIS\n|BASIC with French keywords<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.erudit.org/fr/revues/qf/1983-n50-qf1210773/55407ac.pdf|title=Les langages de programmation|author=Marcel Labelle}}.</ref>\n|\n|-\n|German\n|Teuton\n|A German implementation of [[Python (programming language)|Python]].\n|[http://www.fiber-space.de/EasyExtend/doc/teuton/teuton.htm]\n|-\n|Greek\n|Glossas\n|Based on [[Pascal (programming language)|Pascal]], used for educational purposes in secondary education.\n|[http://alkisg.mysch.gr/]\n|-\n|Hebrew\n|TamliLogo\n|A Hebrew implementation of [[Logo (programming language)|Logo]].\n|[http://www.orianit.edu-negev.gov.il/bagrutcm/cp/homepage/tamlilogo.htm]\n|-\n|Hindi\n|Hindi Programming Language\n|A [[Hindi]] programming language for the [[.NET Framework]].\n|[https://web.archive.org/web/20121001163914/http://www.sktnetwork.com/portfolio/hindi-programming-language]\n|-\n|[[Hindi]], [[Bengali language|Bengali]], [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]]\n|[[Hindawi Programming System]]\n|A set of variants of C, [[C++]], [[Lex (software)|lex]], [[yacc]], [[Assembly language|assembly]], [[BASIC]], [[Logo (programming language)|Logo]] and [[Ada (programming language)|Ada]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Icelandic language|Icelandic]]\n|[[Fj\u00f6lnir (programming language)|Fj\u00f6lnir]]\n|An imperative programming language from 